reviews.text: First I want to say thank you to Taylor and all of the staff at Firehouse Axes.  You were all very kind, patient and helpful from the moment our large group walked in until the time we left. Second,  The food was great,  Throwing axes and stars was great, the atmosphere was fantastic. Third, we had a great time and appreciate you all.  Taylor, you were amazing!!!

Had a great time at the kids axe academy!!  Great games for kids, very patient and awesome axe staff, and great food and drinks!  Wings were so good we ended up with 3 orders!  Great job Firehouse Axes!!

Friendliest servers ( Johnny was our coach too, and really helped me with my throw ), great food, great drinks ( especially the bloody Mary's, Heather mixed me a mean one üëå )... good music, too. Good fun all around! Plus, it is reasonably priced as well

I've gone to firehouse axes twice for special events with a group of friends and the staff has always been friendly, helpful, and just overall great. The food is just slightly overpriced in my opinion, but it is quite good. Aside from the obvious axe throwing, they also have a few other fun group games such as jumbo connect 4.

Cool vibe, great atmosphere, phenomenal customer service. I surprised my husband with a date here as a part of our upcoming birthday celebrations. They graciously accommodated my  custom drink and song request and the food and drinks were excellent They even gave us a little birthday treat, singing happy birthday as they brought them over to us. We will definitely be back. We had so much fun!! Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.text: Me and my Girlfriend stopped here on the way back home from the portland zoo. We had a blast and a wide drink selection including "Mocktails" (Non alcoholic cocktails). detailedReviews.author: Dani Councilman
detailedReviews.text:
Beer, axes, and completive games; what could go wrong? Firehouse Axes provides a superb experience for the whole family where everyone will have a good time.

If this is your first time throwing an axe around, I would suggest starting with an hour and adding more time if necessary. Second, it's best to reserve a spot online to make your experience easier. You do need to sign a waiver before throwing which can be available online as well. You can fill it out at the time of your reservation be sure to have a valid ID upon your arrival.

The staff was welcoming, they take safety seriously but also want you to have a good time. If you're new to throwing, they can provide tips to ensure you have a great time.

I highly recommend coming to throw an axe to a wall and drinking a cold beer with Firehouse Axes. Thank you for a fun time.

detailedReviews.text: This was a pretty fun little spot for a group of us tonight. The axe cages have 3 different axes to throw and cool cages. The food was nothing extraordinary, but it was good. We don‚Äôt think we would come back just because the pricing is what we all 6 considered to be a bit much. A margarita is $10, other mixed drinks are $12.50. $30 per person, per hour for the non-electronic section.
